5px;">CBDCs</h2><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Obviously if you were designin=
g the world from first principles you might say, well, if the government wa=
nts to give people money, it should have a better way of doing that than ho=
ping some tech companies will come along and think =E2=80=9Chey what if we =
advertised on buses?=E2=80=9D For instance if everyone had an account with =
the central bank and the government said =E2=80=9Clet's put $10,000 into ev=
eryone=E2=80=99s account,=E2=80=9D that would do a lot of the work of the P=
PP (not all, certainly) with roughly zero (incremental) administrative cost=
. In the actual world people have accounts at different banks, and some of =
them don=E2=80=99t have bank accounts at all, and there's fraud and blah bl=
ah blah you end up paying $3 billion to some tech companies for administeri=
ng the program. But it is not hard to imagine a world where everyone did ha=
ve an account at a central bank and some of these problems were=C2=A0comple=
tely trivial.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://li=
nk.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24305256.256930/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZmVkZXJ=
